<HEADLINE> ITF Grants Karbacher Wildcard for Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Bernd Karbacher of Germany, who beat
Croatian Goran Ivanisevic to reach French Open quarterfinals here,
has been granted a wildcard entry to the Atlanta Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
A provisional list of Olympic participants, released Thursday
by the International Tennis Federation, shows the 56th-ranked
Karbacher is a wildcard.
</P>
<P>
Karbacher would have missed the Olympics as the German National
Olympic Committee (NOC) said it would not send players ranked out
of the ATP's top-40 except 42nd-ranked David Prinosil.
</P>
<P>
The Olympic tennis competition, which runs from July 23 to
August 3, will lack such big names like Boris Becker and Michael
Stich.
</P>
<P>
The men's singles field features America's world number one
Pete Sampras, reigning Olympic champion Marc Rosset of
Switzerland, Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia and 1988 bronze
medallist Ivanisevic.
</P>
<P>
Seoul Olympics gold medalist Steffi Graf of Germany and Monica
Seles, who shares the world number one ranking, will head the
women's field, which includes French Open finalist Arantxa
Sanchez-Vicario of Spain. 
</P>
