<HEADLINE> Buganda Radio Goes on Air in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 6 (Xinhua)-- Buganda's Central Broadcasting
Service (CBS), a Buganda monarchy-owned radio, offcially went on
air today.
</P>
<P>
The radio at Mengo here, the seat of parliament of the Buganda
Kingdom, is going to be mainly commercial, Patrick Kisuule, Mengo
spokesman told newsmen here today.
</P>
