<HEADLINE> Barkley Might Not Be Back With Suns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Charles Barkley said if he plays
basketball next season, it likely won't be in Phoenix, a report
from Phoenix said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Barkley told NBC in a halftime interview during the first game
of the NBA Finals that More than likely he has played his last
game for the Suns.
</P>
<P>
"I feel like I have earned a certain amount of respect and I
don't like the way they (the Suns) are doing it," he said. "I feel
like I've given them 110 percent for four years. I don't look at
myself like a piece of meat."
</P>
<P>
The Suns acquired Barkley in a trade with Philadelphia four
seasons ago. He won the American National Basketball Association's
Most Valuable Player Award in 1993, when Phoenix lost to Chicago
in the NBA Finals.
</P>
<P>
Barkley, who averaged 23.2 points and 11.6 rebounds in 71 games
last season, said he plans to continue playing basketball for
another year or two before retiring _ but only if the conditions
are right.
</P>
<P>
The Suns were 41-41 last season and then were eliminated in the
first round of the playoffs. 
</P>
