<HEADLINE> WHO to Study Mobile Phone's Effects on Health </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, June 5 (Xinhua) -- After numerous reports on medical
problems caused by mobile telephones, the World Health
Organization (WHO) has decided to conduct a five-year study of
their effect on human beings.
</P>
<P>
The study would investigate whether the phones generate any
magnetic or electrical fields that are hazardous to health, local
press reports said today.
</P>
<P>
However, the WHO emphasized that there is no evidence so far
that mobile phones are harmful to users.
</P>
<P>
Mobile phone sales in Sweden are expected to hit around 900,000
units this year, exceeding the earlier forecast of 665,000
units. Nearly one out of four Swedes has a mobile phone. 
</P>
