<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Software Industry Booms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 6 (Xinhua) -- U.S. software makers are making a
big contribution to the economy, and they're out to make some
noise about it.
</P>
<P>
From 1987 through 1994, the industry grew by 117 percent, while
the rest of the economy grew 17 percent, according to a recent
report of the Business Software Alliance.
</P>
<P>
The industry's revenue reached 74 billion U.S. dollars, the
Washington-based trade group said.
</P>
<P>
Employment also climbed remarkably. American software companies
now employ well over half a million people. From 1992 to 1994
alone, employment rose 9 percent a year, much faster than the
average pace of the nation.
</P>
<P>
And American software publishers dominate their field. U.S.
firms now make three-quarters of the world's software. Nine of the
top 10 firms are American.  
</P>
</TEXT>
