<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 6 (Xinhua) -- A cargo plane crashed as it tried
to take off at Zaire's international airport outside Kinshasa
today and all eight crew were believed killed, a report from the
Zairean capital quoted witnesses as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Russian-built Ilyushin 76 crashed about 200 meters from
the runway and burst into flames, witnesses said.
</P>
<P>
Workers at the airport braved fumes to remove the bodies of
the crew members, believed to be Russian, from the wreckage
before Zairean fire fighters arrived about an hour after the
incident.
</P>
<P>
January 8 this year saw zaire's worst aviation disaster, in
which a Russian-built Antonov failed to take off and crashed into
a crowded Kinshasa market, killing more than 300 people. 
