<HEADLINE> Hezbollah Guerrillas Attack Israel's Buffer Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Guerrillas of the Lebanese
pro-Iranian Hezbollah, or Party of God, carried out today
operations inside the Israeli self-proclaimed "security zone" in
south Lebanon, drawing immediate counterattacks by Israeli forces.
</P>
<P>
In a statement distributed here this afternoon, the Islamic
Resistance, the military wing of the Shiite Hezbollah, said that
one group of its fighters mounted a bomb attack at an Israeli
patrol comprising of two M113 armored vehicles this morning.
</P>
<P>
It said that the guerrillas detonated a "big mine" targeting
the patrol on the road between the villages of Al-Adiseh and Rub
Thalathin in the occupied border strip.
</P>
<P>
"All the Israeli soldiers in the patrol were killed and
wounded," said the Islamic Resistance, the main guerrilla force
engaged in the warfare in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, other Hezbollah guerrillas fired artilleries
at the Israeli post of Talleh Al-Aqaba.
</P>
<P>
The Islamic Resistance noted that some vehicles were parking
inside the post when the shelling started, which led to a serious
damage.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, another group of the Hezbollah fighters launched an
attack at the Israeli position of Beit Yahoun with rockets and
machine guns, causing casualties and damages.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Radio confirmed the guerrilla attacks, but failed to
mention whether casualties were caused.
</P>
<P>
It accused Hezbollah of violating a cease-fire understanding
Israel reached with Lebanon on April 26, which ended a 16-day
Israeli blitz in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The statement of the Islamic Resistance said that following
this morning's operations, Israeli helicopters hovered over Wadi
As-Selouki, tracing the guerrillas and firing intensive and
concentrated shots.
</P>
<P>
The guerrillas "fired back with anti-air weapons and contained
the activities of the helicopters," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Security sources in south Lebanon said that the Israeli
artillery shelled the vicinities of several villages opposite the
buffer zone, and the sporadic bombardments lasted until the
sunset.
</P>
<P>
The U.S.-mediated cease-fire understanding in April bans
attacks at or from civilian areas, but it does not prohibit
Lebanese guerrillas from launching attacks at the Israeli
occupation forces in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
International efforts for the formation of a cease-fire
monitoring committee, provided for in the April understanding,
was cut off by the May 29 Israeli general elections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
