<HEADLINE> Four Injured in Explosion in Istanbul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- An electric transformer station in a
hotel in Istanbul exploded this evening, injuring four people, the
semi-official Anatolia news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the explosion occurred when a technician
tried to cut the current in the electric transformer station in
the underground floor of Mercury Hotel in Asmali Mescit street of
the Taksim district.
</P>
<P>
The technician was seriously injured and the explosion caused
great panic and fire in the hotel.
</P>
<P>
The fire brigade put out the fire immediately and investigation
into the incident is underway, the agency said. 
</P>
