<HEADLINE> Huge Potential Gas Field Found in Vietnam's Red River Delta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Australian company Anzoil has
found a huge potential gas field in northern Vietnam's Red River
Delta.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnam News reported today that the gas field's reserve is
estimated at more than 900 billion cubic feet. It is located in
Thai Binh province, 93 killometres southeast of Hanoi.
</P>
<P>
Test drilling began just three months ago in line with the
first product sharing contract between the National Oil and Gas
Corporation Petro Vietnam and a foreign partner, Anzoil (Asia) of
Australia.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnam News said northern Vietnam is to enter a new era of
cheaper and cleaner energy following an independent evaluation of
the 'commercially significant' gas find last week.
</P>
<P>
According to an Anzoil press release, the gas well has
completed production testing with early indications that the gas
find could be in excess of eight million cubic feet per day.
</P>
<P>
Anzoil has been examining the commercial options for gas
development, the Vietnam news said, adding that it could support a
world-scale power plant, a world-scale methanol export plant or
several other viable commercial possibilities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
