<HEADLINE> Cairo University to Prepare Studies on Antiquity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Cairo University Antiquities and
Environmental Engineering Center will prepare studies on the
repairs of a number of important Islamic and Coptic monuments, the
local newspaper The Egyptian Gazette reported today.
</P>
<P>
This has been approved by Egypt's Higher Council for
Antiquities chaired by Culture Minister Farouk Hosni, the paper
said.
</P>
<P>
Secretary General of the Council Abdul Halim Nour Eddin
announced that the most important monument to be repaired is the
Magra el-Eyoun wall which is a unique water project in Egypt and
the Arab world. The process will be carried out in three stages,
he added.
</P>
<P>
Nour Eddin said another project is to repair "Almusaferkhana,"
a housing unit for visitors and passers-by established in the
Higra year 1195.
</P>
<P>
He said there are also projects to repair Coptic monuments,
including Pope Antonios Monastery in the Red Sea region. The
monastery was the first one established by Pope Antonios, the
founder of Christian monarchism, born in Beni Suef in 251.
</P>
</TEXT>
