<HEADLINE> Turkish Military Exercises Begin in Aegean, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- A planned maneuver of the Turkish
armed forces, codenamed "Sea Wolf 2-96," started this morning in
the bases and ports in Golcuk, Istanbul and Marmaris.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish military exercises, which are taking place in
international waters and air space of the Aegean and East
Mediterranean, are expected to last for 28 days.
</P>
<P>
The six-stage maneuver involves destroyers, frigates,
speedboats, submarines, support ships and helicopters from the
Turkish Navy as well as fighter planes and bombers from the
Turkish Air Force.
</P>
<P>
The military exercises are aimed at carrying out trials of
various battle strategies and developing coordination and
collaboration between the Naval and Air Forces.
</P>
<P>
The military ships participating in "Sea Wolf 2-96" will call
at aksaz, Antalya, Finike, Alanya, Mersin, Iskenderun, Canakale
and Izmir ports as well as the Girne and Gazi magosa ports in
northern Cyprus. 
</P>
