<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 7 (Xinhua) -- After five months in a coma and seven
and a half months into her pregnancy, 30-year-old Dr. Mary Okine
gave birth to a baby girl today at a hospital in Accra, capital of
Ghana.
</P>
<P>
Local newspaper reports said she has been in a coma since last
December, brought on by a viral infection. The reports from
Accra said she had a normal delibery.
</P>
<P>
Although Dr. Okine's condition has not changed, giving birth
may enhance her chances of recovery, according to the reports.
</P>
<P>
She was previously flown to London on May 15 for treatment but
without results.
</P>
<P>
The baby is being kept in an incubator at the Dorle Bu
Hospital in Accra where she was born, according to the Ghanian
Times.
</P>
<P>
The paper said the entire staff in the hospital have been
praying for Dr. Okine who is very popular among patients and
medical personnel at the hospital where she works.
</P>
<P>
When her plight was made known, donations flooded in to help
send Dr. Okine to the United Kingdom for treatment. 
