<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Climb on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined for the
most part of the day but picked up at the closing bell on the
Singapore market amid quiet trading, with the benchmark Straits
Times Industrials index closing at 2338.3 points, up 4.04 points
from Thursday's finish.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume was 78.41 million units, valued at
356.88 million Singapore dollars (about 254.91 million U.S.
dollars). Falls overtook rises by 139 to 125, while 293 other
stocks remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Singapore Telecom was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 7.64 million units. Transmarco was next
with 5.97 million shares traded, while Metroplex saw 5.85 million
of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Asean led the gainers of the day as it picked up by 40 cents to
19 U.S. dollars. SBS Foreign and the Singapore Press Holdings
Foreign each rose by 30 cents to 10.4 and 27.4 Singapore dollars
respectively.
</P>
<P>
FELS was the biggest loser as it declined by 75 cents to 7.8
Singapore dollars. It was followed by the Singapore Press
Holdings, which lost 30 cents to 14.6 Singapore dollars. Bukit
Sembawang was next closing 20 cents lower at 35 Singapore dollars.
</P>
