Minister for Economic Cooperation at the cabinet Youssef Boutros
Ghali along wtih the governor of the Central Bank and heads of the
money market and several banks from Egypt will attend the
conference.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the U.S. Chamber of Commerce in Egypt Shafik Gabr
said that representatives from finacial authorities, investment
companies and multinational companies will review the investment
climate in Egypt, the positive impact of investment in the long
term and using international markets to promote privatization and
economic reform. 
