<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Weakens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar weakened
against major currencies today.
</P>
<P>
It ended at 78.72 US cents from 79.09 US cents on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar was hit by falling commodity prices and
lost ground against other currencies.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar was traded weaker against the Japanese
yen at 85.48 yen from 86.56 yen on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It was also weaker against the German mark, ending at 1.2031
marks from 1.2107 marks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
