<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Stock Market Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Australian stock market took a
breath after falling sharply in the past two days and finished the
week's trade slightly firmer.
</P>
<P>
The All Ordinaries index rose by 6.3 points to 2,220.1 points.
</P>
<P>
The local bourse was traded higher as share prices of major
mining companies rallied.
</P>
<P>
The All Industrials index rose by 6.6 points to 3,271.3 points,
while the All Resources index added 6.3 points to 1,430.3 points.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totaled 332 million shares, valued at 835
million Australian dollars (660 million US dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
