<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Interviewed by Britain's "Financial Times" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng was
interviewed here today by Peter Montagnon, Asia editor of
Britain's "Financial Times."
</P>
<P>
During the 90-minute interview, the premier answered
Montagnon's questions concerning the prospects for China's
economic development, the Chinese government's stand on entering
the World Trade Organization (WTO), Sino-US relations, and the
issues of Taiwan and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Montagnon and his crew arrived in Beijing on June 2 for two
weeks of interviews in China, which will be featured in a special
edition on China by the "Financial Times." 
</P>
</TEXT>
