<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rural Kids in Chongqing Aided by Project Hope </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Since Project Hope was
established here in 1993, residents in this industrial city have
donated 6 million yuan to build 11 primary schools and help more
than 20,000 children return to school.
</P>
<P>
Project Hope is a national program that collects donations to
help dropouts in poverty-stricken areas continue their studies.
</P>
<P>
Among the rural population of 11 million in Chongqing, in
southwest China's Sichuan Province, 580,000 still do not have
sufficient food and clothing. Each year, 10,000 children are not
able to enter schools or are forced to quit due to economic
factors.
</P>
<P>
Project Hope officials in Chongqing said that they focus their
attention on "one-to-one" assistance, meaning one donor supports
one poor child for the entire nine-year compulsory education.
</P>
<P>
"So far, our efforts have met with active response and enjoyed
wide support in the society," said a local Project Hope staff
member, who added that personalities in the city's Buddhist circle
donated more than one million yuan to the children's fund.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
