<HEADLINE> Seven Kilograms of Heroin Seized in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong police seized seven
kilograms of heroin from a residence in Ho Man Tin, Kowloon, last
night, a police spokesman said today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that following in-depth investigations and a
week's surveillance, the police raided a flat at Oi Man Estate and
seized seven kilograms of heroin which have a market value of
about 3 million HK dollars (387,000 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
One man was arrested. Police also seized some additives and
packaging equipment for drugs, he said.
</P>
<P>
Police believe they have smashed a dangerous drugs packaging
and distribution center and the drugs were to be supplied to the
Kowloon East market.
</P>
<P>
The 41-year-old man, who was suspected to be trafficking in
dangerous drugs, was arrested inside the premises.  
</P>
</TEXT>
