<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK External Trade Rises Slightly in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The volume of Hong Kong's
re-exports increased by 7.5 percent in the first three months of
this year compared with the same period last year, while the
domestic exports dropped by 7.4 percent, according to the Census
and Statistics Department.
</P>
<P>
Taking re-exports and domestic exports together, the volume of
total exports grew by 4.9 percent. Meanwhile, imports increased
by 5.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
As regards price changes over the period, the prices of
re-exports and domestic exports rose by 1.2 percent and 1.8
percent respectively. Import prices increased by 1.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Comparing March 1996 with March 1995, the volume of re-exports
fell by 4.9 percent, while that of domestic exports dropped by 20
percent. Taken together, the volume of total exports fell by 7.4
percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the volume of imports was down by 1.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
The prices of re-exports and domestic exports increased by 0.7
percent and 1.8 percent respectively. Import prices rose
marginally by 0.6 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
