<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Taxi to Reach 715 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MACAO, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The number of taxis in Macao will
reach 715 in about four months time, according to a report in
today's Macao Daily News.
</P>
<P>
Currently, there 686 taxis running through the streets in
Macao, but the number will increase to 715 as dozens of new taxi
licences were given out earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
The Macao City Government auctioned 30 taxi licences in April
this year, and the licences were sold out at price as high as some
1.7 million Patacas (about 215,000 US dollars) at the maximum
price.
</P>
<P>
Macao's taxis are divided into two kinds, the black ones and
the yellow ones. The yellow taxis belong to a certain company, and
are available of service through telephone calls.
</P>
<P>
Macao's taxi drivers charge passengers nine Patacas (One US
dollar is about 7.9 Patacas) for the first 1,500 meters, and the
fare increases by one Pataca for every 220 meters after the first
1,500 meters. There are also extra fares for passengers destined
to islands or leaving from the airport.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
