<HEADLINE> Japan Provides Fund for Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, June 7 (Xin hua) -- Japan has decided to grant over 5
million U.S. Dollars to assist Mozambique in promoting its
drinking water-providing program in the rural areas of Gaza
Province in the south, "Noticias" reported today.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed when Japanese Ambassador Asaou Tsukahara
conveyed his credentials to President Joaquim Chissano at the
presidency here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
As Ambassadors to both Zimbabwe and Mozambique and based in
Harare, Tsukahara came specially from Harare to call on the
Mozambican president, and an agreement on the grant had been
signed in Harare on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
During the interview, Tsukahara hoped Japan would provide
Mozambique with aid in building and rehabilitating bridges
damaged during the civil war.
</P>
<P>
A Japanese experts team has been in the country for several
weeks to look into the matter and it will provide assistance in
rehabilitating at least 13 bridges, the paper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
