<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila Gears Up for Massive Infrastructure Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines is gearing up for a
massive infrastructure development program in a bid to sustain the
country's strong economic growth.
</P>
<P>
For the first five months this year, infrastructure projects
registered with the Board of Investments (BOI) reached 39.843
billion pesos (1.59 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
At present, the BOI is eyeing the registration of at least 150
billion pesos (6 billion US dollars) worth of infrastructure
projects this year.
</P>
<P>
This is 20 billion pesos (800 million US dollars) higher than
the 130 billion pesos (5.2 billion US dollars) worth of
infrastructure projects registered last year.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the telecommunications sector, which bagged the bulk
of investments, witnessed the registration of nine projects with a
total project cost of 74 billion pesos (2.96 billion US dollars).
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
