<HEADLINE> Japan to Release Loans to Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Japan will release some 24 billion
pesos (960 million US dollars) worth of the remaining official
development assistance (ODA) loans for the Philippines, a Japanese
senior diplomat here said today.
</P>
<P>
He said the Japanese government is ready to release the funds
once the final obstacle to the loan disbursement is removed.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese embassy in Manila has kept Tokyo up to date on the
development of the ODA bill, which was approved Thursday by the
Bicameral Conference Committee of the Philippine Congress.
</P>
<P>
The diplomat said Japan respects the decision of Filipino
legislators that the Philippine government must get prior
approvals from congress for projects to be financed by ODA funds.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
