<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Exports Grow 21 Percent in First 4 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' merchandise exports
reached 6.175 billion US dollars in the first four months of the
year, up 21.1 percent from the 5.101 billion US dollars posted in
the same period last year, the National Statistics Office said
today.
</P>
<P>
For April alone, revenues of the merchandise exports totaled
1.490 billion US dollars, the office said.
</P>
<P>
Electronics and components remained the country's top earners,
which grossed 618.92 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The United States and Japan continued to be the largest buyers
with purchases amounting to 489.27 million US dollars and 230.88
million US dollars respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
