<HEADLINE> Iran Thwarts US Embargo, Rafsanjani </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani today claimed victory over the Unites States, saying
the one-year-old trade embargo against his Islamic Republic had
totally failed.
</P>
<P>
He told a Friday prayers session on Tehran University campus
that the fact was recognized by all economic and social analysts
even those inside the United States.
</P>
<P>
The United States imposed sanctions against Iran a year ago to
punish it for alleged support for international terrorism and
efforts to produce nuclear weapons.
</P>
<P>
"We are not under such conditions that the sanctions of the
U.S. and others could have considerable impact on us and we
ourselves can manage our life," the president said.
</P>
<P>
The president did not provide details to prove his claim but
it was clear that Washington eventually has been confronting
Tehran lonely since its such traditional allies like France,
Germany, Japan, Italy and even Britain are still buying Iranian
crude.
</P>
<P>
France's Total, ignoring US pressure to stay out of Iran,
signed a 600 million dollar agreement with Iran in last July,
thus replacing American company Conoco to develop the Sirri A and
E offshore oil fields in the Gulf.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, Russia, Iran's neighbor in the north, has
made much progress in expanding its cooperative relations with the
Islamic Republic.
</P>
<P>
Moscow has not only scratched an one-billion- dollar nuclear
project in Iran despite strong opposition from the Washington but
also turned itself to oil business with Tehran.
</P>
<P>
Iran, a country with a population of 65 million, pumps out
3.65 million barrels of oil and exports about 2.5 million barrels
daily.
</P>
<P>
President Rafsanjani said:"Today the Islamic Republic of Iran
has gained dignity, respect and honor whereas the U.S. has been
humiliated and disgraced." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
