<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Weekly Report on China's Material Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- China's material market in the past
week was stable, but a little sluggish, with prices of major
materials coming down or remaining unchanged, except for the
pick-up in steel materials, according to China Materials
Information Center.
</P>
<P>
Of the 39 varities of steel products monitored by the Center
under the Ministry of Internal Trade, 23 recorded rises in prices;
14 witnessed downs; and two remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The average price for 6.5mm steel wire rod was quoted at 2,827
yuan (340.6 US dollars) per ton, up seven yuan; that for 20mm
screw thread steel was 2,722 yuan per ton, up 11 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Of the nonferrous metals, copper was quoted at an average of
26,419 yuan per ton, down 87 yuan; aluminium was 16,747 yuan per
ton, down six yuan; lead was 7,239 yuan per ton, up 31 yuan; and
zinc was 9,793 yuan per ton, up 15 yuan.
</P>
<P>
On the chemical materials market, prices for major products
including plastic material, organic material, and inorganic
products continued the down-turn trend. For example, high-pressure
polyethylene was quoted at an average of 9,214 yuan per ton, down
181 yuan; low-pressure polyethylene was 8,894 yuan per ton, down
22 yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
