<DOCNO> XIE19960607.0102 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Twelve Scientists Won Engineering Science, Technology Awards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Twelve scientists today received
China's first ever Engineering Science and Technology Awards in
Beijing, in recognition of their outstanding contributions to the
country.
</P>
<P>
The oldest award winner was Shen Hong, 93, an expert in
mechanical engineering and academician at the Chinese Academy of
Engineering.
</P>
<P>
In the 1960s, he headed a research team which designed and
produced China's own train wheels and tyres, putting to an end the
country's long dependence on foreign imports for the equipment.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Xinsong, an automation expert, won the award as one of
the pioneers of China's robot industry. He founded the State Robot
Technology Research Center, as well as a robot laboratory of the
Chinese Academy of Sciences.
</P>
<P>
He is also playing a key role in the country's development of
industrial robots, underwater robots, and robots with other
special functions.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Guangdou, described as the founder of China's water
engineering, obtained the honor for providing valuable technical
consultation for dozens of major water projects across the
country, including the Gezhouba Dam and the Three Gorges' Dam.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Guangya, president of the Chinese Academy of Engineering
and chairman of the China Engineering Science Awards Foundation,
said at the awarding ceremony that all the winners well deserved
the great honor.
</P>
<P>
"They have made outstanding contributions to the country with
their knowledge and specialities over a long period of hard and
persistent work," he noted.
</P>
<P>
The 12 award winners were chosen from 79 candidates by a
special panel formed by some 100 academicians, he revealed.
</P>
<P>
The China Engineering Science and Technology Award was founded
a year ago, with the purpose of rewarding and encouraging
scientists who make conspicuous achievements or significant
contributions to the country in the field of engineering science
and technology as well as management.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
