<HEADLINE> Stich Eliminates Rosset to Enter Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Michael Stich downed Marc Rosset in
straight sets of 6-3, 6-4, 6-2 on Friday to move into the men's
final of the French Open, his third grand slam final.
</P>
<P>
Stich will face the winner of the other men's semifinal Friday
between top-seeded Pete Sampras of the United States and
sixth-seeded Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia in Sunday's final.
</P>
<P>
The 15th-seeded German, who earlier upset defending champion
Thomas Muster, took the match in just one hour, 35 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Stich, 27, broke the Swiss Olympic Rosset, 14th seed here, four
times, but never lost his own serve.
</P>
<P>
The German won Wimbledon in 1991 and lost the U.S. Open final
to American Andre Agassi in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Stich also becomes the first German to reach the men's final
at the French Open since Henner Henkel won in 1937.  
</P>
