<HEADLINE> Ten Italian Policemen Detained for Corruption </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Ten Italian policemen were detained
Thursday in the southern port city of Naples, accused of
protecting organized crime and accepting bribes, local press
reports said Friday.
</P>
<P>
An investigation showed that the policemen, including an
officer, have since 1994 put under their protection a local gang
engaged in highway robbery and theft. In return, the gang handed
over cash ranging from 320 to 2,000 U.S. dollars per week to the
policemen.
</P>
<P>
The case is the most serious incidence of police corruption in
Naples' history, said the reports, which also claimed that crimes
involving law enforcement officers were racking the whole nation.
</P>
<P>
If convicted, the policemen will be subject to harsh penalties
and a ban for life from jobs in justice and security agencies.
</P>
</TEXT>
