<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-foreign Motorcycle Joint Venture Goes into Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- China's largest Sino-foreign joint
venture to build motorcycles has gone into production in Zhuzhou,
Hunan province.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture, Zhuzhou Southern Yamaha Motorcycle Company,
has been built jointly by Yamaha Engine Corporation of Japan, and
the Power Machinery Company under China Southern Airlines. The
total investment of 60 million US dollar has been shared equally
by the two sides.
</P>
<P>
With an annual production capacity of 200,000 motorcycles, the
company is equipped with six production lines, which were built
with the latest Japanese technology. It covers 150,000 square
meters and has a combined floor space of 59,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
The second project, the Zhuzhou Southern Yamaha Damper Company,
has been built jointly by Yamaha Corporation of Japan, China
Southern Airlines and Xiangling Machinery Plant with a total
investment of 18 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The first construction phase with an investment of about 10
million yuan has been completed, and the company is producing
300,000 sets of damper products a year. Its annual production
capacity is expected to reach 900,000 sets by the end of this
century.
</P>
<P>
At present China has 110 motorcycle manufacturers with an
annual production capacity of 7.8 million motorcycles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
