<HEADLINE> Turkish RP Leader to Be Assigned to Form New </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Turkey's pro-Islamic Welfare Party
(RP) leader Necmettin Erbakan is expected to be assigned this
evening by President Suleyman Demirel to form a new coalition
government, Turkish sources told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that Demirel would meet with Erbakan at the
presidential palace at 15:00 GMT and give him the mandate to form
the government.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish president will appoint Erbakan to form the
coalition after Motherland Party (ANAP) Chairman and Prime
Minister Mesut Yilmaz submitted his resignation to Demirel
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Yilmaz stepped down as the Turkish Constitutional Court has
announced that the vote of confidence in March for the
center-right coalition government between the ANAP and True Path
Party (DYP) was unconstitutional and DYP Chairwoman Tansu Ciller
decided to withdraw her support for the government led by
Yilmaz.
</P>
<P>
After the general elections in December, Demirel assigned
Erbakan, leader of the party that appeared at the top of the
elections, to form a coalition government in January. But Erbakan
did not succeed in his talks with four other political party
leaders to seek partnership for the coalition and returned the
mandate to Demirel. 
</P>
