<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- General Fu Quanyou, chief of the
general staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army, held talks
in Beijing today with Benedito Onofre Bezerra Leonei, chief of
staff of the Brazilian armed forces.
</P>
<P>
They exchanged views on the reinforcement of contacts between
the two armed forces and other issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Fu said that the PLA treasures its contact with the Brazilian
armed forces, and expressed the conviction that Leonei's visit
would help deepen understanding between the two armed forces and
promote bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that the PLA is willing to have more exchanges
with the armed forces throughout the world, including those of the
Latin American countries, in a bid to improve understanding and
friendship as well as contributing to the peace of the world.
</P>
<P>
Fu expressed appreciation for the Brazilian government's
consistent adherence to the "one China" policy. He reiterated
China's opposition to the attempt of any country having diplomatic
relations with China to establish official links with Taiwan or to
conduct official exchanges and contacts with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Leonei agreed with Fu on the necessity to have more exchanges
between the two armed forces, expressing the hope to achieve much
in this respect and to learn more about China's economic, social
and cultural conditions through the current visit.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China, as a big country, is playing an important
role in world affairs, and it is of great significance to
reinforce contacts and co-operation with China. 
