<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japanese Business Confidence Shows Improvement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 7 (Xinhua) -- A Bank of Japan survey released today
showed that business confidence in the country improved
dramatically in May.
</P>
<P>
The central bank's quarterly survey of economic enterprises, or
"tankan," looks at business confidence and is considered a clue to
monetary policy.
</P>
<P>
The survey indicated that the diffusion index for large
manufacturers increased to minus three in May from minus 12 in
February when the bank released its previous survey.
</P>
<P>
The diffusion index measures the difference between the number
of companies with a positive outlook towards the economy and those
with negative projections. The lower the index, the less the
business confidence.
</P>
<P>
The central bank said it expects the diffusion index to be zero
when it conducts its next survey in September, the first time the
index will be out of negative territory in four-and-a-half years.
</P>
<P>
But analysts said the May survey result was not cheery enough
to prompt the central bank to raise interests rates soon from
their current rock-bottom levels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
