<HEADLINE> China's Largest Bank Arranges Special Loans for Textile Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- China's largest bank, the
Industrial and Commercial Bank of China, is to arrange seven
billion yuan in special loans for textile enterprises to help them
operate normally.
</P>
<P>
The loans will enable Chinese textile enterprises to store up
350 million kg of cotton, said a bank official, who added that the
first batch of 2.4 billion yuan in loans has already been extended
to textile enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The official explained that the loan decision has been made in
accordance with the instruction of the State Council, or the
cabinet, to ensure the normal operation of the textile industry.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Xiao, the bank governor, recently made an inspection tour
of north China's Hebei Province, which will be the largest
beneficiary of the loan arrangement, to emphasize that loans are
properly handled.
</P>
<P>
She also called bank subsidiaries at all levels to closely
cooperate with related departments in order to make sure that the
special loans are used to purchase cotton instead of being
diverted for other purposes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
