<HEADLINE> "Blue Line" to be Marked for Olympic Marathon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Olympic Marathon course in
Atlanta, United States, will be marked on Sunday with the "blue
line", which traditionally indicates the shortest distance runners
may follow during the race.
</P>
<P>
According to a news release on Friday, a team of experts from
Columbia, South Carolina who laid down the "blue line" for the
U.S. women's Olympic trials last February, have volunteered to
mark the Atlanta course.
</P>
<P>
Olympic organizers said the marking job, which is expected to
last four hours, will be done with a special striping machine
along the 42.195 kilometers course. 
