<HEADLINE> Captured Salamander Given Freedom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, June 7 (Xinhua) -- A giant salamander, netted by two
Chinese fishermen, can peacefully live in its habitat, a reservoir
near Guiyang, capital of southwest China's Guizhou Province. The
fish was saved by five local farmers.
</P>
<P>
Long Renxing and four villagers from Mutou Village, Yunguan
Towship of Guiyang's Nanming District, saw two fishermen catching
the big salamander at the side of Sancha River on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The farmers told the fishermen that the animal was under top
state protection, and successfully persuaded them to free it.
</P>
<P>
Some experts from the Guizhou Provincial Forestry Department
said the salamander, which was 1.1 meters long and 26 centimeters
wide, weighing 15 kilograms (33 pounds), was rarely seen in the
province. 
</P>
