<HEADLINE> Fatal Traffic Accident Falls to 25-year Low in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The number of fatal traffic
accidents in Hong Kong has reached its lowest point in 25 years,
according to the Road Safety Council.
</P>
<P>
There were 66 fatal accidents between January and April this
year, a sharp decrease of 20 percent compared with the same period
of 1995. However, traffic accident casualties are still high, said
a spokesman of the council.
</P>
<P>
The council will launch a campaign on pedestrian safety
targeting at the elderly next year. There are about 580,000
elderly people aged 65 and above in Hong Kong, who are physically
weak, vulnerable to injuries and unaware of road safety rules and
practices.  
</P>
</TEXT>
