<HEADLINE> Myanmar Promulgates New Law Banning Destabilizing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar State Law and Order
Restoration Council today promulgated a new law banning all
activities which may disturb the peace and stability in the
country, the state-run Radio Myanmar reported tonight.
</P>
<P>
According to the new law, the government shall ban any act
which may disrupt the national reconciliation and the on-going
national convention.
</P>
<P>
Individuals who break the law shall be sentenced to 5 to 20
years' imprisonment. Organizations which break the law shall be
banned.
</P>
<P>
The law was promulgated at the time when tension is running
high between the Myanmar authorities and Daw Aung San Suu Kyi's
National League for Democracy, observers here said.  
</P>
