protection, Wang said, "We should never promote economic growth at
the cost of the environment, and never should we follow the cycle
of pollution first and then environmental control."
</P>
<P>
Many parts of China are affected by water shortages, but they
are still polluting their precious water resources, he said,
adding that "We may cry for thirst in the future if we cannot
control water pollution." 
