<HEADLINE> 97 Major Criminal Suspects Caught in Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Police in south China's Guangdong
Province have caught 97 major criminal suspects since the national
anti-crime campaign started on April 28.
</P>
<P>
On May 12, Li Donghua and Li Liangming, two brothers who
swindled 200 million yuan from several financial institutions in
Wuhan, capital city of central China's Hubei Province, were both
caught in Foshan city, Guangdong.
</P>
<P>
Chen Jialong, who has been on the most-wanted list of the
Ministry of Public Security, had been at large ever since he
deliberately injured others in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
