<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Desert Locusts Seen in Nairobi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Desert locusts have invaded
Nairobi, the capital city of Kenya, according to Kenya's
entomologists.
</P>
<P>
Some of the invading locusts are seen on parking metres, while
others on parked vehicles, the entomologists reported.
</P>
<P>
Street children in Nairobi said they are busy collecting the
rare insects for a feast.
</P>
<P>
An Entomologist of the Desert Control Organization of East
Africa, Dr Tessema Megenasa, said on Thursday "this is the first
case reported to us in Nairobi and we are going to make
arrangements with the Ministry of Agriculture so that the insects
can be controlled."
</P>
<P>
"However, at the moment, I can just describe them as a
temporary disturbance in the city, but they can wreak havoc, if
they moved to upcountry farms, " warned the doctor.
</P>
<P>
The case is the second to be reported in the country this
year, after the pest in the semidesert area north of Marsabit
District. 
</P>
</TEXT>
