<HEADLINE> (Correction) Bomb Blasts Lusaka International </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Another bomb blast took place in
the Zambian capital of Lusaka on Thursday night, but this time,
at the Lusaka international airport. One police officer was
killed and another wounded.
</P>
<P>
The local radio broadcast said this morning that the device
exploded at about 21:00 hours (local time) on the first floor of
the terminal building, leaving debris of glass on the tarmac and
pavement.
</P>
<P>
The blast came one day after the detonation of an explosive
device at the city's Freedom Way on early Wednesday, when
businesses nearby were disrupted for hours, without reports of
casualties or serious damage.
</P>
<P>
The latest bombing is the fourth in the country since a secret
group named "Black Mamba" threatened to use violence against the
recent passing of a controversial constitution ammendment bill,
which deprives former Zambian president Kenneth Kaunda of
qualifications for the presidential election slated for October
this year.
</P>
<P>
The first two explosions occurred at a state house wall in
Lusaka and at the "Times of Zambia" office in the central city
of Ndola. 
