<HEADLINE> Africa Needs Strong Financial Sector: Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Africa needs a strong and vibrant
financial sector to support its industrial development,
Zimbabwe's Minister of Finance Herbert Murerwa said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Opening a two-day all-Africa banking and financial services
conference, Murerwa urged delegates to refocus their strategies
in order to gear themselves for the challenges presented by the
new global business environment.
</P>
<P>
"It is therefore imperative for african countries to upgrade
technologies through investments in computer hardware and
software, emphasizing skills development,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
The conferfence, organized by computer giant IBM, has drawn more
than 200 bank and business executives as well as senior government
officials from Africa and Europe. 
</P>
