<HEADLINE> Uganda Registers 2,171 New Investments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Uganda Investment Authority
(UIA) has recorded 2,171 new investments in the east African
nation since UIA was set up in 1991, reported the local newspaper
"The Monitor" today.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the UIA on Wednesday was quoted as
saying that 60 percent of the project investments are made by
Ugandans.
</P>
<P>
But of the total proposed and licensed investments, worth
2.835 billion US Dollars expected to create 115,737 jobs, only
about 35-45 percent are actually on the ground, according to the
statement.
</P>
<P>
Yet A.K Karemente, a UIA official, is still holding "the flow
of investment is quite encouraging" and of the estimated 1,750
projects licenced, the number of take-offs is satisfactory. 
