<HEADLINE> Russian Iranian Officials Start Talks (by Chen Ming) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
TEHRAN, June 7 (Xinhua) -- High-ranking officials from Russia
this morning started talks here with Iranian officials on various
issues ranging from the Middle East crisis, Afghanistan and
Tajikistan.
</P>
<P>
An informed source told Xinhua that Russian Deputy Foreign
Minister Viktor Posuvalyuk arrived here early in the morning and
now is holding talks with Iranian Deputy Foreign Minister Mahmoud
Vaezi.
</P>
<P>
The source, who declined to be identified, said that the two
sides will also explore the way for Tehran-Moscow cooperation in
the Caspian Sea.
</P>
<P>
The visiting Russian Deputy Foreign Minister is expected to
hold talks with Iranian Foreign Minister Ali Akbar Velayati
tomorrow. He is scheduled to depart on Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
The source said the exchange of views on the developments in
the Middle East was on the agenda of Posuvalyuk's visit to Tehran.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian government regards Posuvalyuk's visit to Tehran
"politically important," the source added.
</P>
<P>
Posuvalyuk's visit is seen here as an effort to prepare for a
meeting between Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeni Primakov and his
Iranian counterpart Ali Akbar Velayati.
</P>
<P>
The Russian official will also visit Baghdad, Amman and
Damascus after his stay in Tehran.
</P>
<P>
He is expected to study Russia's economic cooperation with Iraq
in the wake of signing an oil-for-food deal between Iraq and the
United Nations.
</P>
<P>
Posuvalyuk will also deliver a message from Russian Foreign
Minister Yevgeni Primakov to Iraqi Deputy Prime Minister Tareq
Aziz. 
</P>
</TEXT>
