<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Gold Output Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 7 (Xinhua) -- More than 8,200 kg of gold worth
over 100 million US Dollars were produced in Zimbabwe during the
first four months of this year, the daily Herald reported today.
</P>
<P>
Over the same period last year, local mines produced 7,441.7
kg valued at 76.1 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe, Africa's third largest gold producer after South
Africa and Ghana, last year mined more than 24 tonnes valued at
260 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Last year's output of gold, a major foreign currency earner
after tobacco and tourism, was the highest in five decades in
Zimbabwe. enditem

