<HEADLINE> Uganda's GDP Growth Stands at 7.8 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's real growth rate of gross
domestic product (GDP) stands at 7.8 percent in this fiscal year
(July 1, 1995 -- June 30, 1996) compared with the programed 5.6
percent, reported the local newspaper "The Monitor" today.
</P>
<P>
Ulrike Wilson, resident representative of the International
Monetry Fund (IMF), was quoted as saying the growth rate figure
had gone up due to the increase in production of coffee which is
the country's main earner of foreign exchange and the expanding
manufacturing sector.
</P>
<P>
The GDP growth for last fiscal year in Uganda stood at 10
percent, one of the highest in Africa. 
</P>
