<HEADLINE> Xining Zoo Haven for Rare Animals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Xining Zoo has successfully bred
a variety of rare animals unique to the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau,
such as black-necked cranes and snow leopards.
</P>
<P>
The zoo, located in the capital city of northwest China's
Qinghai Province, is the largest of its kind on the plateau.
</P>
<P>
Due to the plateau's deteriorating natural conditions, the
population of many rare animals has dropped sharply, and some are
nearly extinct, prompting Xining Zoo to intensify the research and
breeding of the unusual species.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, zoo authorities have undertaken several
national breeding projects. Xining Zoo is the first in the world
to successfully artificially breed the black-necked crane, which
is under state protection. And it is the first in China to breed
the snow leopard, also state protected. Scientists there also have
artificially bred several wild donkeys and Siberian tigers.
</P>
</TEXT>
