<HEADLINE> New Major Oil Field Under Construction in Junggar Basin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a major oil field
with an anticipated annual output of 400,000 tons of crude has
started in the Junggar Basin of northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The Shixi Oilfield is the country's second largest in desert
area, following the Cainan Oilfield in the same basin, that has an
annual production capacity of one million tons.
</P>
<P>
According to an official with the Xinjiang Petroleum
Administration, the first oil well of the Shixi Oilfield was sunk
last August, producing a daily output of 130 tons, representing
the highest yield in the entire whole basin area.
</P>
<P>
The Shixi Oilfield, discovered in the late 1980s, covers an
oil-bearing area of 37 sq km with oil deposits topping 34 million
tons, according to a geologist with the administration.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the oil field is rich in natural gas. A gas pipeline
extending from Shixi to Karamay is now under construction, and is
scheduled to be completed this October. 
</P>
</TEXT>
