<HEADLINE> Moves of First Game in Karpov-Kamsky Match </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Following are the moves of the
adjourned first game of the World Chess Championship between
Russian Anatoly Karpov and American Gata Kamsky in Elista on
Thursday with Karpov playing white:
</P>
<P>
1. d4 Nf6; 2. c4 g6; 3. Nc3 d5; 4. Nf3 Bg7; 5. Qb3 dxc4;
6. Qxc4 0-0; 7. e4 Nc6; 8. Be2 Bg4; 9. Be3 Bxf3; 10.Bxf3 e5;
11. d5 Nd4; 12. Bd1 b5; 13. Nxb5 Nxe4; 14. 0-0 a6; 15. Nc3 Nd6;
16. Qd3 Qh4; 17. g3 Qh3; 18. Bxd4 exd4; 19. Ne2 Qf5; 20. Nf4 Rfb8;
21. Qxf5 Nxf5; 22. Nd3 Bh6; 23. Rel a5; 24. Bg4 Nd6; 25. Re2 a4;
26. a3 Ra5; 27. Rc2 Rxd5; 28. Rxc7 Ra5; 29. Bf3 Bg5; 30. Rdl Rc8;
31. Rxc8+ Nxc8; 32. h4 Bf6; 33. Rcl Nd6; 34. Kf1 Be7; 35. Ke2 Kf8;
36. Rc7 Bf6; 37. Kd2 h5; 38. Ke2 Nf5; 39. Rc4 Nd6; 40. Rb4 Ra6;
41. Nc5 Ra7; 42. Kd3 Rc7; 43. Nxa4 Rc1; 44. Nb6 Bg7; 45. a4 Ra1;
46. Nd7+ Ke8; 47. Nc5 Ke7; 48. Kc2 Rf1; 49. Nd3 Ra1; 50. Kb3 f5;
51. Rb6 Bh6; 52. Bd5 g5; 53. Ra6 gxh4; 54. gxh4 Rd1; 55. Bc4 Rh1;
56. a5 Rxh4.  Match adjourned.  
</P>
