<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Senior People Seek Help in "Conversation Rooms" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 7 (Xinhua) -- In a simply-furnitured room at a
neighborhood committee elderly people sit together, talking about
their troubles, and getting comfort and help from each other.
</P>
<P>
Granny Yang, an 84-year-old widow, has made the "conversation
room" her second home. She knows she can always get help from
friends and neighborhood committee members.
</P>
<P>
"The neighborhood committee members cooked three meals for me
every day while a heart disease made movement difficult for me,"
she said.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai, the first city in China to face the problems of an
ageing population, now has 1,200 "conversation rooms" where senior
citizens can meet with new friends they have made.
</P>
<P>
Gong Nenghai was feeling low and depressed, when he came to the
room for "heart to heart talks". He was suffering with his
crippled leg.
</P>
<P>
A member of the neighborhood committee found through
conversation that he was not getting along well with his wife, and
helped him find ways to reconcile.
</P>
<P>
Gong bid farewell to the friends in the conversation room and
the neighborhood committee members reluctantly last year, and
moved to another district with his happy family.
</P>
<P>
Since Yanzhong neighborhood committee set up the first
"conversation room" in the city, which has 2.2 million people aged
60 and over, the number of such rooms surged to 1,200 and the ways
of conversation in those rooms multiplied.
</P>
<P>
Elderly people can have person to person chats, or group
conversations in the rooms, to help their feelings of loneliness
and receive advice and help for problems.
</P>
<P>
A service network for the senior people has taken shape in the
city, with a volunteers' service group for each social community,
and the activity halls, matrimonial agencies, health care clinics
and family wards for the elders.
</P>
<P>
Old people's universities and activity centers were also
established in the city to provide a happy and colorful life for
the residents in their later years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960607.0205 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Company Joins with Hilton to Build Luxury Hotels in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- A leading Chinese real estate
developer will work together with British-based Hilton
International to establish 20 five-star hotels in China over the
next 20 years.
</P>
<P>
This marks the first large-scale joint effort between a Chinese
company and an overseas hotel group.
</P>
<P>
The China International Industry and Commerce Corporation Ltd.
(CIIC) has signed a contract with the British company, CIIC
vice-president Hu Jiafang revealed here today.
</P>
<P>
The two groups have plans for nearly 100 three-star hotels, he
said.
</P>
<P>
China now has only 40 five-star hotels; two of them, in Beijing
and Shanghai, belong to Hilton.
</P>
<P>
According to Hu, the new hotels will be located in central
cities, newly-opened areas, and new and well-known tourist
attractions.
</P>
<P>
The three domestic bases of CIIC -- Beijing, south China's
island of Hainan, and east China's coastal areas including
Shanghai -- will be given priority as building sites, he said.
</P>
<P>
The 123,000-square-meter State Guest Garden, which was
developed by the CIIC Beijing Branch, will convert half of its
acreage into a five-star hotel. This land was bought by Hilton
International with 228 million U.S. dollars last month, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
Most of the extensive funding necessary for the hotels will be
collected internationally by Hilton, which will manage the hotels,
according to the contract.
</P>
<P>
CIIC, Hilton's sole agent in China, will invest in the
preparatory work, including site construction, and will be in
charge of development of all projects.
</P>
<P>
With combined fixed assets of more than five billion yuan, CIIC
claims Class-A authority for real estate development,
architectural design, construction supervision, and import and
export trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
