<DOCNO> XIE19960607.0206 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tennis Top Players to Compete in Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Tennis top players Pete Sampras of
the United States and Steffi Graf of Germany will spearhead their
respective countries to compete in the coming Olympic Games in
Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
Among the line-up for Atlanta announced by the International
Tennis Federation on Thursday, are men's defending champion Marc
Rosset of Switzerland and Monica Seles who shares the women's top
rank with Graf.
</P>
<P>
However, women's Olympic champion Jennifer Capriati of the
United States was not in the roster due to her poor ranking.
Capriati just returned to the court after a hiatus of two years
due to drug and personal problems.
</P>
<P>
Also in the men's field were third-ranked Andre Agassi of the
United States, Goran Ivanisevic of Croatia who won the bronze
medal in Barcelona, Sergi Bruguera of Spain and Thomas Enqvist of
Sweden.
</P>
<P>
The women's group includes Spain's Arantxa Sanchez Vicario and
Conchita Martinez.
</P>
<P>
In Atlanta, 35 squads will compete in the men's singles, with
32 in women's singles and four wild cards to be named later.
</P>
<P>
Among the big names who skip the Olympics include Germans Boris
Becker and Michael Stich, Swedish Stefan Edberg and American
Michael Chang. 
</P>
</TEXT>
