<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Expects Surge in Real Estate Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 7 (Xinhua) -- A surge in real estate
development is expected to start here this year, according to
local sources.
</P>
<P>
Figures recorded for the first quarter of 1996 in real estate
construction volume, utilization of foreign investment and sales
of commercial housing, show a 62 percent rise over the same period
last year in this capital city of south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The growth is attributed to the expansion of the State financial
reform and the designation of Guangzhou as one of the country's
center cities.
</P>
<P>
Real estate has proved to be one of the major economic
industries in Guangzhou. By the end of 1995, the city had
established over 1,100 real estate enterprises, including 280
foreign-funded enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The cumulative real estate construction volume topped nearly 58
billion yuan, with the completion of more than 17 million sq m of
housing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
