<DOCNO> XIE19960607.0209 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Over 1,000 Ancient Tombs Found in Hebei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- More than 1,000 ancient tombs from
the Warring States Period (476-221 BC) to the Han Dynasty (206
BC-25 AD) have been found at the construction site of an iron and
steel complex in Handan City, central China's Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
Chinese archaeologists have excavated 300 of the tombs and
unearthed more than 1,000 pieces of bronze, jade, bone, shell and
pottery.
</P>
<P>
Among the relics the experts valued was a bronze hook decorated
with agate and carnelian.
</P>
<P>
However, the experts said that the tombs belonged to ordinary
people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
