<HEADLINE> Beijing Implements Development Plan About Women </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- A charter to help women climb the
ladder of success has been announced in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Municipal Committee of the Communist Party of China
and the Beijing Municipal Government have issued a development
plan for women.
</P>
<P>
The plan's aim is to protect the legal interests of women,
promote overall development of women, and standardize and guide
Beijing's work on women.
</P>
<P>
The plan has 11 major work targets concerning women.
</P>
<P>
They cover women's participation in state affairs, cultural
education, employment, health care, family planning, protection of
women's legitimate rights, development of rural women, promotion
of exchanges between domestic women organizations and between
domestic and overseas women organizations. The last target is to
establish statistics on development concerning women.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the ratio of women cadres of Beijing is
11.6 percentage points higher than the national average, and the
highest in the country.
</P>
<P>
The number of educated women is among the highest among the
country's cities, provinces and autonomous regions.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 100 percent of school-age girls have attended schools.
</P>
<P>
Beijing now has 1.84 million working women, 39 percent of the
total number of workers. The women are serving in agriculture,
industry, commerce, culture, education, health care, finance and
many other sectors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
