<HEADLINE> Panama, Chile to Promote Technical, Scientific Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Panama and Chile signed an
agreement here Thursday on promoting technical and scientific
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by acting Panamanian Foreign Minister
Ricardo Alberto Arias and visiting Chilean Foreign Minister Jose
Miguel Insulza.
</P>
<P>
During their talks, they also expressed their belief that
Panama can well manage the Panama Canal alone after assuming its
administration in January 1, 2000.
</P>
<P>
The United States has controlled the Panama Canal since 1903,
but it will return full responsibility to Panama by 2000 according
to the 1977 Torrijos-Carter Treaty. 
</P>
