<HEADLINE> Caucasus Peace Festival Closes in Vladikavkaz </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 6 (Xinhua) -- An international festival, held with
the theme of "Let Caucasus Have Peace", closed in Vladikavkaz in
the Russian republic of North Ossetia today.
</P>
<P>
Present at the festival were artists, musicians, playwrights,
actors, actresses and directors from Russia, Azerbaijan, Armenia,
Georgia and from nearby Caucasian regions.
</P>
<P>
The participants of the festival expressed peace wishes and
swapped views through various parties, performances and forums.
</P>
<P>
It was the first fraternal activity held in the Caucasus where
territorial disputes and bloodshed among ethnic minorities took
place time and again in the past.
</P>
<P>
Russian President Boris Yeltsin sent a message of
congratulation to the festival. He said that Caucasus will have
peace thanks to the efforts of artists as well as statesmen.
</P>
