<HEADLINE> Cuba, Spain Seek to Strengthen Business Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Spain and Cuba are to strengthen
bilateral trade and business ties after a meeting between the two
countries' business people.
</P>
<P>
The sixth annual meeting of the Spanish-Cuban business
cooperation committee signed an agreement reviewing the
opportunities for Cuban economic growth and expressing the desire
to expand and strengthen bilateral trade relations.
</P>
<P>
Alberto Betancourt, a Cuban trade official, said that many
Spanish people have come to Cuba to do business and economic
cooperation has been broadened over the last few years.
</P>
<P>
Spain is one of the countries with the most developed economic
relations with Cuba. Two-way trade reached more than 400 million
U.S. dollars last year, with an increase of more than 40 percent
over the previous year. 
</P>
