<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Number of Taxis in Macao to Reach 715 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MACAO, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The number of taxis in Macao will
reach 715 in about four months time, according to a report in
today's Macao Daily News.
</P>
<P>
Currently, there are 686 taxis running through the streets in
Macao, but the number will increase to 715 as dozens of new taxi
licenses were given out earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
The Macao City Government auctioned 30 taxi licenses in April
this year, and the licenses were sold out at prices as high as
some 1.7 million Patacas (about 215,000 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Macao's taxis are divided into two kinds, the black ones and
the yellow ones. The yellow taxis belong to a certain company, and
are available for service through telephone calls.
</P>
<P>
Macao's taxi drivers charge passengers nine Patacas (One US
dollar is equal to about 7.9 Patacas) for the first 1,500 meters,
and the fare increases by one Pataca for every 220 meters after
the first 1,500 meters. There are also extra fares for passengers
destined to islands or leaving the airport.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
