<HEADLINE> British Co. to Launch Operations in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Associated British Foods (ABF)
announced today that it will launch two joint venture operations
in northern Chinese province of Henan.
</P>
<P>
With initial joint investments of about 10 million U.S. dollars
each, the programs call for the construction of a new glucose
plant and a pharmaceutical dextrose plant.
</P>
<P>
ABF will take a 51 percent share in both of them.
</P>
<P>
The first program, to be launched with China's Lianhua Gourmet
Powder Company, aims to produce 50,000 tons of refined glucose
from native maize starch each year.
</P>
<P>
The facility will be operated by the Henan Lianhua BSO Glucose
Company Limited.
</P>
<P>
The second program, to be carried out by the Henan Lianhua BSO
Pharmaceutical Company Limited, will build up an annual production
capacity of 24,000 tons of dextrose.
</P>
<P>
Calling the programs "exciting ventures," Garry Weston, ABF's
chairman, said the company was "delighted" to have established the
partnership in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
