<HEADLINE> Olympic Tickets Printed Wrong Times </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 6 (Xinhua) - Numerous sports fans may miss the
games should they stick to the time table in their tickets due to
changes of competition schedules at the Atlanta Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Organizers said on Thursday that some 170,000 Olympic tickets
were printed with wrong times, including those for the events of
handball, track and field, women's basketball, beach volleyball,
fencing and modern penathlon events.
</P>
<P>
Those ticket holders for the August 4 handball finals, were
even in a trap of not seeing any player because the match was to
be started four hours earlier.
</P>
<P>
However, the organizers will issue a Games guide to all, which
will highlight the time changes. 
</P>
