<HEADLINE> Karpov Draws First Game in Defense of World Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Russian world champion Anatoly
Karpov offered for a draw in the first of the 20-game series FIDE
World Championship on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Played in Elista, Kalmyk Republic, Karpov, 45, initiated the
game with a d4 pawn, and American challenger Gata Kamsky, 22,
responded with the Grunfeld defense.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the end of the game, both players were left with a
rook, a bishop, a knight and three pawns each, with Karpov in a
clear advantage as his pawns were spread in dangerous spots.
</P>
<P>
The series is scheduled to continue on Friday, and the first
who scores 10.5 points will become the new world champion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
