<HEADLINE> Bullish Trading on Dhaka Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Trading on the Dhaka Stock Exchange
(DSE) dramatically turned bullish in the past week after dull
trading in the previous week.
</P>
<P>
According to sources concerned, the DSE price index jumped
21.47 points to 886.33 points last week ending Thursday from
previous week's closing of 864.86 points as most of the traded
issues posted gains.
</P>
<P>
Market capitalization reached highest in the DSE history,
breaking all previous records and standing at TK 60.18 billion
(1.5045 billion US dollars) on Thursday from previous week's TK
58.72 billion (1.468 billion dollars), the sources said.
</P>
<P>
A DSE member said that investors were more active in the week
as they anticipated that Bangladesh's June 12 general elections
would be held on schedule without any major incident and the
confidence had propped up the market from bearish trend.  
