<HEADLINE> Singapore Stock Exchange to Launch New Index </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Stock Exchange of Singapore
(SES) will launch a new regional stock index in the second half of
this year, the local newspaper Business Times reported today.
</P>
<P>
It said the Singapore Finance Minister Richard Hu told an
international conference in Tokyo on Thursday that the regional
index would provide investors and fund managers with a meaningful
benchmark to track and measure the performance of their portfolios
in regional stocks listed on the SES.
</P>
<P>
