<HEADLINE> Figures Don't Reflect Real AIDS Situation in Czech Republic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The number of people with AIDS in
the Czech Republic could be at least 10 times greater than the
official statistics show because most sufferers are too ashamed to
go for medical help, the country's Health Ministry has said.
</P>
<P>
Some 266 people have been found suffering from AIDS and 59 have
died of the disease since 1986, a spokesman told Xinhua. In 1995
alone, 40 new cases were recorded, with four fifths of sufferers
aged between 13 and 34, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
