<HEADLINE> Continental Air Forces Chiefs' Meeting Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The chiefs of air forces
from 19 Latin American countries here today concluded a four-day
meeting aimed at strengthening military cooperation among them.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was the 36th Conference of Commanders-in-chief of
American Air Forces (Conjefamer).
</P>
<P>
At the annual conference, the chief of the Argentine Air Force,
Brig. General Juan Paulik and his Bolivian counterpart General
Rafael Berzain Rodriguez stressed the importance of cooperation
among the armed institutions in the continent.
</P>
<P>
Conjefamer meets once a year to consider proposals suggestions,
and projects that would benefit its air forces members. 
</P>
