<DOCNO> XIE19960607.0259 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OPEC Adjourns Session for Differences Over Iraq, Quotas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The OPEC ministers adjourned its
Vienna conference until Friday after four hours' discussions today
on how to cushion the return of Iraqi oil and realign its
"obsolete" quota distributions.
</P>
<P>
The 100th conference of the 36-year-old Organization of
Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC), a half-yearly regular event,
opened its first session today after a one-day delay.
</P>
<P>
OPEC Secretary-General Rilwanu Lukman said today's session went
"fairly well," coming to deal with the adjustment of output levels
to manage Iraq's revived oil export under a United Nations accord
ending its 1990 Gulf War embargo.
</P>
<P>
Under the May 20 accord, Iraq will gain 2 billion U.S. dollars
by exporting an average of 0.7-0.8 million barrels a day (MBD) for
six months to buy food and medicine.
</P>
<P>
This sum, coupled with the long-existing overproduction by some
OPEC members which have lifted their real output some 1.5 MBD
above the 24.52 MBD ceiling, is feared to deal a heavy blow to the
already vulnerable oil prices.
</P>
<P>
The OPEC's package of oil prices have already dropped below 19
dollars per barrel by now since April when it broke down the
designated reference 21 dollars.
</P>
<P>
Some members suggested OPEC, now pumping 26 MBD, move up its
somewhat obsolete three-year-old ceiling, to about 25.5 MBD, while
several others demand bigger quotas.
</P>
<P>
In this case, a decision on reallocating quotas or raising the
ceiling is widely expected in Vienna.
</P>
<P>
Gabon has reportedly threatened to withdraw from the oil cartel
in protest against its indiscriminate appropriation of yearly two
million U.S. dollar membership fees regardless of the countries'
different liabilities, as was yet to be confirmed.
</P>
<P>
Accounting for 40 percent of the world's total oil output every
year, the OPEC's proven reserves amount to 70 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
