<HEADLINE> China Donates Farm Machines to Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIGALI, Rwanda, June 6 (Xinhua) -- China today donated 625,000
U.S. dollars worth of farm machinery and pesticides to Rwanda to
help its reconstruction and develop agricultural production.
</P>
<P>
Rwandan Agriculture Minister Augustin Iyamuremye said at the
donation ceremony that his country is grateful to China for its
timely help and that the two countries can expand friendly
cooperation in agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Rwanda, in central Africa, is an agricultural country and 70
percent of its agricultural production had been restored by the
beginning of this year after nearly two years of reconstruction
following the end of the three-month civil war in June 1994.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese donation included rice mills, oil presses,
threshers, sieving machines, sprayers, spare parts and
pesticides. 
</P>
