<HEADLINE> Mercosur, EU to Discuss Commerce Liberalization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Progressive and reciprocal
liberalization of commerce between the South American Common
Market (Mercosur) and the European Union (EU) will be discussed on
June 10-12 by foreign ministers of members of the two trade blocs
in Luxembourg and Brussels.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first meeting after the Interinstitutional
Agreement of Economic and Commercial Cooperation was signed by the
two parties in December 1995 in Madrid, Spain, the Brazilian
Foreign Ministry announced today. The agreement foresees yearly
meetings of the respective foreign ministers.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian Foreign Ministry said that the inter-regional
association of the four-member Mercosur and the 15-nation EU might
get stronger after the year 2005, when the Americas' Free Trade
Zone starts operating.
</P>
<P>
A major obstacle between the two sides is the liberalization of
their most sensible areas: industry for Mercosur and agriculture
for the EU. 
</P>
</TEXT>
