<HEADLINE> Thailand to Suspend Tariff Cuts on Textiles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Thai Prime Minister Banharn
Silpa-archa has told the Finance Ministry to suspend import tariff
reductions within one week on textiles, garments, leather and
shoes, the local press reported.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister's request came after the private sector
warned at a recent meeting between the public and private sectors
that the tariff cuts would hurt those industries.
</P>
<P>
The Finance and Industry Ministries were asked to work together
to seek ways to comply with the request. But Finance Minister
Bodi Chunnananda said more time was needed to reconsider effects
of tariff cuts on all 13 categories of luxury goods.
</P>
<P>
The Thai cabinet on May 7 approved a Finance Ministry proposal
to cut tariffs on the 13 categories of luxury goods, including
textiles, garments, leather bags and shoes, and cosmetics, which
triggered off a strong opposition from the private sector.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said that tariffs rates on textiles, garments, leather
and shoes might revert to old ones.
</P>
<P>
So far, of the 13 categories, only cosmetics have been imported
since the announcement of the tariff cuts.  
</P>
</TEXT>
