<DOCNO> XIE19960607.0268 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rare, Endangered Plants Find Home in Botanical Garden </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Huanan Botanical Garden in
Guangzhou, capital of south China's Guangdong Province, has become
the world's biggest research center for plants in the lily
magnolia family.
</P>
<P>
Plants of lily magnolia family are believed to be primitive in
nature. Around the world there are some 250 species in 15 generas
belonging to the family. In China, there are more than 150 species
in 11 generas.
</P>
<P>
Most of the plants are 14 to 40 meters high, which constitute
the higher level plants in forests and play a vital role in
maintaining an ecological balance.
</P>
<P>
Their elegant canopies and beautiful flowers also make them
ornamental plants in gardens.
</P>
<P>
However, many species are endanged or even on the verge of
extinction.
</P>
<P>
Starting from 1950s, the Huanan Botanical Research Institute
has been engaged in collecting plants of lily magnolia family, and
has conducted investigations on the distribution and biological
features of such plants in 14 Chinese provinces and regions since
1977.
</P>
<P>
In 1981 the research institute set up a lily magnolia area
covering 12 hectares within the Hunan Botanical Garden, aiming to
introduce and multiply plants in the lily magnolia family.
</P>
<P>
The garden now boasts 6,700 plants belonging to 120 species in
11 generas of the family, including 38 rare or endangered
species.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960607.0269 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Anhui Blueprints Export-oriented Economic Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, June 7 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province has
worked out a strategic plan to accelerate its export-oriented
economy and hook into the international market.
</P>
<P>
According to the plan, cities along the Yangtze River such as
Ma'anshan, Wuhu, Tongling and Anqing, as well as the provincial
capital of Hefei, are encouraged to further develop their
export-oriented economy and lead the province in cooperation and
competition within the international economic market.
</P>
<P>
A provincial official said that areas provided with convenient
transport facilities should make use of their advantage to become
favored places for foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
And the province will guide foreign investment in building
projects characterized by advanced and practical technology and
better economic return.
</P>
<P>
Anhui has vowed to increase its foreign trade by an annual 26.6
percent and to use four billion US dollars of foreign investment
during the 1996-2000 period.
</P>
<P>
It had imported and exported 2.3 billion US dollars worth of
goods in the 1991-1995 period, and used 1.91 billion US dollars
during this period.
</P>
<P>
At present, the province has more than 3,400 foreign-funded
enterprises, including a number of transnational corporations.
</P>
<P>
It plans to boost machinery, electric appliances, electronics,
automobile, chemicals and building industries by the end of this
century.
</P>
<P>
While developing star enterprises and brand products, Anhui
will rearrange its economic patterns in line with local
conditions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
