<HEADLINE> Chengdu Encourages High-tech Industrial Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Chengdu High-tech Industrial
Zone in this Sichuan province capital is expected to expand from
2.5 square kilometers to 40 square kilometers.
</P>
<P>
This growth is part of the city's efforts to create better
conditions for high-tech industries and prove itself a leader in
local economic development.
</P>
<P>
A committee of administrative and judicial departments has been
set up to better manage the zone and foster its growth.
</P>
<P>
An exchequer system has been established within the zone, and
all charges collected from it will be retained within the area for
construction costs.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1991, the zone has imported 494 projects, of which
148 were foreign-funded. During the 1991-95, it generated output
value totalling 7.67 billion yuan and profits and taxes amounting
to 1.7 billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
