<HEADLINE> China Builds David's Deer Protection Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, June 7 (Xinhua) -- China has invested 2.65 million yuan
on the construction of a David's deer protection zone in central
China's Hubei province.
</P>
<P>
So far almost a third of the whole project has been
completed. Work on building a 2,500-meter long and one meter wide
anti-flood platform is progressing smoothly before the arrival of
the flood season.
</P>
<P>
In 1987 the State Bureau of Environment Protection selected 138
hectares of marshland in Shishou city's Tian'ezhou, beside the
Yangtze River, to use as a David's deer protection zone.
</P>
<P>
The zone began to breed David's deer in 1993. There are now 105
of the deers in the zone.  
</P>
</TEXT>
