<DOCNO> XIE19960607.0281 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Baby-Friendly Action in East China County </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Yinxian County in east China's
Zhejiang province has launched an action campaign to create the
country's first baby-friendly county.
</P>
<P>
The county plans to popularize knowledge on the irreplaceable
nutrition of mother's milk and the special significance of breast
feeding in maintaining love between mothers and babies.
</P>
<P>
The county has also asked relevant departments and local
hospitals to strictly implement breast feeding according to
international norms, and allow mothers and their newly-arrived
babies to stay in same rooms all day long.
</P>
<P>
As a result the ratio of four-month old babies who are breast
fed has increased by 25 percent compared with three years ago.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile the incidence of baby diarrhea, pneumonia and breast
mastitis has dropped markedly.
</P>
<P>
Yinxian county, one of the richest in China, has set up a
leading group specially in charge of promotion of baby-friendly
action.
</P>
<P>
The county has developed a regulation stipulating that local
medical institutions will not be allowed to recommend or promote
the selling of baby milk substitutes.
</P>
<P>
All work units are being asked to guarantee maternity leave and
daily breast feeding times for new mothers.
</P>
<P>
Units with women accounting for the most part of labor force
must build baby-friendly rooms, and township and village level
clinics which have less than ten delivery beds are asked to
install more beds, according to the regulation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
