<HEADLINE> Wage Purchasing Power Falls in New Zealand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The purchasing power of wages
and salaries in New Zealand fell slightly in the March 1996
quarter compared with the December 1995 quarter, Statistics New
Zealand said today.
</P>
<P>
In the latest quarter under review, the After-tax Wage Rate
Index (AWRI) rose 0.4 percent. But it was offset by a 0.5 percent
increase in the Consumers Price Index (CPI).
</P>
<P>
In the year to March 1996, the after-tax wages and salaries for
New Zealanders rose 1.8 percent. But the Real Wage Rate Index
dropped 0.4 percent as the CPI went up 2.2 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
