<HEADLINE> Book on Mongolian Military Thoughts Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HUHHOT, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Mongolian History of Military
Thoughts has been published by the China Military Science
Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
The book sums up the military experience of Genghis Khan and
his successors' conquest of Mongolia and China during the Yuan
Dynasty (1271-1368), and the lessons which caused the decline of
the dynasty.
</P>
<P>
It also gives an account of the merits of major military
figures along Mongolian history at that time.
</P>
<P>
The 70-year-old author Da Lintai has retired from the military
area of Inner Mongolia. He has been engaged in researching the
military thoughts of Mongolians.
</P>
<P>
In 1990 he published a book entitled Mongolian Military Science
Studies. 
</P>
