yesterday reported a surge in tourists in the last three months of
1995, with the numbers exceeding one million for the first time.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Financial Review
</P>
<P>
-- Prime Minister John Howard will next week press state
premiers to immediately implement a new regime of "competitive
federalism" which could see states offering radically different
health and community services.  
