<HEADLINE> Nigerian Palm Oil Project Underway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria has completed arrangement
for the development of 600 hectares of land for oil palm
cultivation in eastern Taraba State, according to the National
Agricultural Land Development Authority.
</P>
<P>
The project, when fully developed, will provide half of the
nation's industrial and local palm oil requirement as well as
bring down the current high price of the commodity, said
Christopher Danjuma, state director of the agency, quoted by the
News Agency of Nigeria today.
</P>
<P>
So far contract for the clearing and development of the 600
hectares land has been awarded, with 359 hectares developed and
another 200 hectares planted, he added.
</P>
<P>
About 500 farmers in the state have shown their willingness to
participate in the program, which the official described as "very
viable", according to the report. 
</P>
