<DOCNO> XIE19960607.0306 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rwanda Hopes To Strengthen Friendly Ties With </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
(By Pei Shanqin)
</P>
<P>
KIGALI, June 6 (Xinhua) --Rwandan President Pasteur Bizimungu
today expressed the hope that friendly co-operation between
Rwanda and China will be further strengthened.
</P>
<P>
President Bizimungu will start a five-day official visit to
China on June 10 at the invitation of President Jiang Zemin of
the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first time for him to visit China since he
became president of Rwanda on July 19, 1994.
</P>
<P>
On the eve of his tour to China, the president stressed, in an
exclusive interview with Xinhua, that there exists profound
friendship between Rwanda and China.
</P>
<P>
He said, after the end of the civil war and genocide in July
1994, the Rwandan new government faced arduous work to undertake
all tasks neglected and to reconstruct the homeland.
</P>
<P>
"It is at this difficult time that China has given precious
assistance politically, morally and materially to Rwanda," he
said. China was one of the first countries which resumed their
embassies' work in Kigali in the post-war time, he added.
</P>
<P>
On the aim of his forthcoming visit to China, President
Bizimungu said: "I'm going to China, firstly to express my
government and my people's gratitude to China, and then, to
reinforce this friendship and co-operation between the two
countries."
</P>
<P>
The president said that he will, during the visit, brief
Chinese leaders and people on the efforts and the progress made
by his government in the reconstruction of homeland and
rehabilitation of economy after the end of the civil war and
genocide in the country.
</P>
<P>
He said that the internal situation in Rwanda has became calm
and the security situation obviously improved. "Rwanda has forged
ahead a decisive step along the road to build and strengthen
peace and social security and to reconstruct and rehabilitate the
economy in the country," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
However, President Bizimungu said, despite about 1.8 million
old and new refugees have returned back home, more than 1.5
million refugees are still staying abroad.
</P>
<P>
"There is a lot to be done for the national reconciliation and
reconstruction in the country," he said.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the president said, Rwanda hopes to continue
getting support from China, adding that the Rwandan people need
more support from China, especially at the time when they are
facing numerous difficulties on the road of economic
rehabilitation and reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
President Bizimungu expressed his belief that by his visit,
the friendly co-operation between Rwanda and China will be
further strengthened. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
