<DOCNO> XIE19960607.0307 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Market Demand for Forex Dives in Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The demand for foreign exchange at
the Nigeria Swap Market fell sharply today as only a total of
23.63 million US Dollars was in need by banks.
</P>
<P>
The amount was down by more than 50 percent from the 49.039
million Dollars level registered at the autonomous foreign
exchange market.
</P>
<P>
The market started to be under a weekly intervention by the
Central Bank of Nigeria three weeks ago, at an exchange rate of
82.50 Naira against one Dollar.
</P>
<P>
Transaction at the market amounted to 101.5 million Dollars in
the previous week of the central bank intervention, which is
aimed at boosting reform of the country's foreign exchange
system.
</P>
<P>
Tony Ede, corporate affairs manager of the central bank, said
today that the Apex Bank selected 77 banks for taking part in
today's trading at the autonomous foreign exchange market, but
only 49 participated with 28 others opting out.
</P>
<P>
Banks were active in participating in trading at the market
and demand for foreign exchange was on the rise before the
central bank intervention, according to industry sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
